Balancing Risk and Capacity in Hospital Care
ğŸš€ Problem Statement

Hospitals struggle to manage patient flow and care escalation in real time because:

Patient conditions change continuously

Beds, staff, and resources are limited

Decisions rely on static rules and manual coordination

This results in:

Overcrowded emergency rooms

Delayed or premature escalation

Inefficient use of critical resources

Core problem:
There is no intelligent system that can continuously observe, reason, and adapt decisions as hospital conditions evolve.

ğŸ’¡ Our Solution

We built an Agentic AI system for hospitals that:

Uses LLMs + rule-based intelligence

Continuously reasons about:

Patient risk

Resource availability

Staff workload

WHO safety thresholds

Supports dynamic decisions instead of static dashboards

This system acts like a digital care coordinator, supporting doctors, nurses, and administrators in real time.

ğŸ§  What is â€œAgentic AIâ€ here?

Our system is agentic, not just predictive, because it:

Observes evolving patient data

Reasons about multiple constraints

Takes actions (recommendations, escalations, scheduling)

Revisits decisions as conditions change

Each responsibility is handled by a specialized agent.

